RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 63. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RELUCTANT forwardly placed into the first turn, kept close attendance to the moderate pace, confronted the pacesetter nearing the quarter marker, assumed command in upper stretch, was confronted by PEACEHAVEN nearing the sixteenth-marker, determinedly dug in in deep stretch and held on for the win. PEACEHAVEN raced four wide into the first turn then was allowed to settle in the two path in the early stages, advanced to be well positioned along the backstretch run, came within aim nearing the quarter marker, mounted a three wide rally leaving the second turn, closed well inside of the furlong marker, confronted RELUCTANT nearing the sixteenth-marker, battled against the determined winner while on the left lead and was denied for the win, while well clear of the rest. CHELINA rated off of the early pace, saved ground to the far turn, could not keep pace with the top pair in the drive but kept on in the final strides to secure the show. CAL ROUGH stalked the early pace, raced three wide along the backstretch run, was outrun approaching the top of the lane and did not mount a late rally. FUNKY GREY sent to the early lead, set a pressured pace while carving out moderate fractions, was confronted nearing the quarter marker, could not keep pace in upper stretch and faded in the drive. VALDINI bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, unhurried in the early stages and did not factor in the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Chelina
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated off pace,saved ground,needed more stretch,up for show

ENTRY.NAME: Reluctant
ENTRY.OWNER: Rancho San Miguel and Adams, Mike

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 81. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. BOLD DAUGHTER forwardly placed in the early stages, advanced to duel with LION'S LAIR to the quarter marker, battled with that rival to mid-stretch, was held at bay by LION'S LAIR in deep stretch and just missed for the win and place, while clear for show. DRESS REHEARSAL disputed the early pace while inside of LION'S LAIR, lost ground on the turn and did not rally in the stretch run. HEAT SEEKING LETA chased the moderate early pace, raced three wide on the turn, swung four wide for the drive and did not threaten in the late stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 68. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLUBHOUSE WAVE came under a snug hold while just off of the early pace, advanced while in tight nearing the quarter marker, swung three wide for the drive, closed in mid-stretch, headed DADDYS NINA nearing the sixteenth-marker and determinedly prevailed over that rival in the final strides. DADDYS NINA tracked the moderate early pace, saved ground through the turn, advanced in upper stretch, took a narrow lead inside of the furlong marker, met the bid of CLUBHOUSE WAVE nearing the sixteenth-marker, was gamely bested by the determined winner in the final strides and was second best. PETE'S INFERNO broke alertly, raced close up to the moderate pace, came three wide to the quarter marker while vying for the lead, battled to mid-stretch, could not keep pace with the top two in the late stages and held for show in the end. TYCHE AWAITS YOU was bothered at the start when ZAKKIYYAH lunged leaving the break and was off a step slowly, unhurried in the early stages, steadied off of heels entering the turn, not far back nearing the top of the lane, swung five wide for the drive, improved position in the final furlong but lacked the needed late response. ZAKKIYYAH lunged at the start, impeded TYCHE AWAITS YOU and was off a bit slowly, rushed up to the lead in the early stages, set a pressured pace on the turn, could not match strides in the final furlong and tired late.

ENTRY.COMMENT: lunged start,rushed up,set pressured pace,tired late

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUNSET PAYNTER broke slow and lagged at the back of the field while saving ground to the turn, began to pass horses inside of the three furlong marker, swung out and circled the field, entering the stretch run in the six-path, then commenced a bold rally down the middle of the track and was up in plenty of time. GET MY POINT tracked the dueling leaders to the turn, hooked a game HOT LINK in a battle the length of the stretch, got the best of that rival in the end but was passed on the outside by the winner in the shadow of the wire. HOT LINK close early, began a bid passing the half mile pole, tipped out to the three path in the stretch to challenge the leader, was in turn joined by GET MY POINT for the stretch run and battled that one to the wire only to be out finished for the place. DRINKUP BUTTERCUP broke alertly and was sent to the front, dueled to the turn with STANDFORGRIT to the inside, opened up a clear lead on the turn, came into the stretch in the two path racing greenly, still fought on gamely but tired in the final furlong. MO TOWN GAL outrun early, came under a mild ride from the five furlong pole, made a mild late bid and managed to split the field. SHE'S FANCY LIKE stayed to to the inside from the break, was not able to keep up with the early pace, re-rallied from the half mile pole, tipped out for the stretch run but was unable to find another gear. STANDFORGRIT away well and contested the early pace, was unable to match strides with STANDFOR GRIT from the three furlong pole, hung in there for a bit but tired from earlier efforts. WHEREDIDITGO lacked early speed, raced wide down the backstretch, came under a hard ride with three furlongs to run, steadied briefly when SUNSET PAYNTER passed in front of him, mustered a bit of a late surge while switching to the inside and finished up evenly while unable to improve position. LUCKY LOCKETT was up close early tracking the dueling pacesetters, never found another gear passing the three furlong pole and fell back.
